einvigorating a long tradition and moving beyond it. What he offers is nothing short of a way to reorient our lives in relation to the divine and our fellow humans. Written from within the Jewish tradition, Fragile Finitude is intended for readers across the religious spectrum.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 0aHermeneuticsxReligious aspectsxJudaism. 7aRELIGION / General.2bisacsh  aJewish theology, hermeneutical theology, lived experience, ritual practice, spiritual practice, midrashic theology, mystical theology, ethics, PaRDeS.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Complete eBook-Package 2021z978311073919040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226764290423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780226764290/original  a978-3-11-073919-0  University of Chicago Complete eBook-Package 2021b2021  aGBV-deGruyter-alles